rch-based-refinement/external/OpenLtm-main/docs/internal/DB-SPEC.md:\n  Line 5: **Status:** Current schema spec against plugin v2.8.0\n\n  Line 9: This document is the authoritative reference for the LTM plugin data tier. It covers\n\n  Line 45: The core table. Every durable insight the plugin has stored, whether from `learn`,\n\n  Line 102: | `workspace_id`, `agent_id` | Multi-agent isolation (ROADMAP Phase 5 / T16); both indexed |\n\n  Line 1014: ### Phase 5 — Cross-Plugin Contract (v2.0.0, semver-major)\n\n  Line 1016: Goal: stable versioned MCP write surface; registry fully in DB.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/OpenLtm-main/docs/internal/ROADMAP.md:\n  Line 15: **Where we are (v1.4.20):** A working LTM plugin with SQLite + FTS5 + 4 hooks + 7 MCP tools + grouped commands. Functional. Honest weaknesses: silent hook failures, hand-rolled migrations, O(N) recall, no provenance, no audit, no observability. UX is invisible-by-default but onboarding is \"abandoned by 50%\".\n\n  Line 17: **Where we want to be:** A magnificent LTM that is invisible when it should be, surgical when invoked, trustable for teams and enterprise, and pluggable for embeddings, sync, bundles, and cross-plugin contracts.\n\n  Line 19: **The plan:** 8 phases (v1.5.x → v2.2.x). Phases 0–4 are non-breaking foundation. Phase 5 (v2.0.0) is the semver-major cross-plugin contract. Phases 6–7 layer on team/enterprise/power-user features.\n\n  Line 38: | Cache vs source dual-write | — | W6 | (Phase 5) | §6.4 lifecycle | — |\n\n  Line 49: | Cross-plugin contract | G-M | — | C7 | §8.7 surfaces | TBD §9 (versioning) |\n\n  Line 125: **Exit criteria:** plugin works fully without any embedding provider · with provider, recall latency stays < 200ms p95 · explainer shows score breakdown.\n\n  Line 131: **Goal:** The plugin curates itself. Decay, compression, cleanup happen as background work.\n\n  Line 145: ### Phase 5 — Cross-Plugin Contract (v2.0.0, semver-major)\n\n  Line 147: **Goal:** LTM becomes a contract. Other plugins read/write memories through a versioned interface.\n\n  Line 151: | Arch | C7 Cross-plugin memory contract (versioned MCP API + capability discovery) |\n\n  Line 152: | PRD | G-M cross-plugin memory contract |\n\n  Line 157: **Exit criteria:** another plugin can recall+learn through the contract without coupling · breaking changes documented in MIGRATION.md · all UX-SPEC §7 deprecations sunset.\n\n  Line 203: - Drop `:memory:` subnamespace by Phase 5\n\n  Line 252: | Phase 5 | §1 contract | `projects`, `hook_events` tables stabilised at 2.0.0 |\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/OpenLtm-main/docs/internal/PRD.md:\n  Line 3: **Version:** 1.1 (against plugin v2.8.0)\n\n  Line 15: gotchas. The LTM plugin gives Claude — and the developer driving it — a **durable,\n\n  Line 42: | G4 | Survive plugin updates and machine moves | DB at known path, JSON export, schema migrations versioned and idempotent |\n\n  Line 63: Curates their own Claude Code config (hooks, skills, plugins). Wants memory to\n\n  Line 64: **compose** with other plugins, not fight them. Cares about: schema stability, MCP\n\n  Line 90: The cross-session JTBDs the LTM plugin solves:\n\n  Line 103: | J10 | The plugin breaks (hook silent-fail, MCP missing) | Run one diagnostic and get a fix list | Not lose a day debugging meta-tooling |\n\n  Line 168: - **Cache mirror:** `~/.claude/plugins/cache/ltm/ltm/<version>/` — the plugin loader reads\n\n  Line 173: - **MCP server** (`src/mcp-server.ts`) — primary tool surface, started by Claude Code per `mcpServers` in `plugin.json`.\n\n  Line 255: ### US-9 — Diagnose the plugin in 60s\n\n  Line 263: **As** Pat after pulling a new plugin version, **I want** a safe schema upgrade path.\n\n  Line 266: - **Given** the DB schema is at version N and the plugin expects N+1, **when** I run `/openltm:admin migrate`, **then** all pending migrations apply in a single transaction and the schema_version row updates.\n\n  Line 316: ### US-17 — Survive plugin upgrade\n\n  Line 317: **As** Sam clicking \"Update now\" in the plugin marketplace, **I want** my memories preserved.\n\n  Line 320: - **Given** `openltm.db` exists and is at schema vN, **when** the plugin updates to a version expecting vN+1, **then** the next session auto-runs the migration (or prompts) without data loss.\n\n  Line 366: After a non-trivial commit, the plugin prompts: \"Capture the reasoning behind this\n\n  Line 391: ### G-M — Cross-plugin memory contract\n\n  Line 392: Publish a stable read-API so other plugins (e.g., dev-team task-tracker, code-review)\n\n  Line 410: The plugin will not, in this PRD horizon:\n\n  Line 423: - **N8.** Replace the `task-tracker` MCP, the `context-mode` MCP, or any other plugin's\n\n  Line 480:   a Claude Code-native panel via a future plugin UI surface?\n","metadata":{"matches":55,"truncated":false},"title":"Phase.?5|write surface|write contract|stable|learn\\(|cross-plugin|plugin","time":{"start":1780925637715,"end":1780925637732}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0a9ba8164e110900016a26c4c574b0819a9c27d7f9be31a6a3"}},"id":"prt_ea770a450001AUZr0fnKT66TO8","sessionID":"ses_158903c24ffeYh4HmE3B8vB3CW","messageID":"msg_ea7705e5f001sWCBuAz6egdmFS"}}
