{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780925723814,"sessionID":"ses_158903c24ffeYh4HmE3B8vB3CW","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_QIvVT1HYqkFX3jfmdf6SeMQg","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/OpenLtm-main/docs/internal/PRD.md","offset":35,"limit":90},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/OpenLtm-main/docs/internal/PRD.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n35: ### 1.2 Goals (12-month horizon)\n36: \n37: | # | Goal | How we know |\n38: |---|------|-------------|\n39: | G1 | Eliminate cross-session amnesia for active projects | 95%+ of sessions on an active project start with relevant context auto-injected |\n40: | G2 | Make recall faster than re-derivation | Median `recall` round-trip < 200 ms; user reports \"saved me from re-debating X\" |\n41: | G3 | Keep the developer in flow | Zero mandatory prompts; all LTM ops are background or 1-keystroke |\n42: | G4 | Survive plugin updates and machine moves | DB at known path, JSON export, schema migrations versioned and idempotent |\n43: | G5 | Be safe by default | No secret ever lands in the DB; redaction on write; scan command for retroactive cleanup |\n44: | G6 | Be debuggable in 60 seconds | `/openltm:doctor` and `/openltm:health` give a complete plain-English status |\n45: \n46: ### 1.3 Non-vision (explicit)\n47: - This is **not** a team-shared knowledge base (yet). Memory is per-developer-per-machine.\n48: - This is **not** a replacement for git, code comments, or design docs. It captures the\n49:   **reasoning behind** the code, not the code itself.\n50: - This is **not** a model — it is a retrieval and curation layer over a local SQLite store.\n51: \n52: ---\n53: \n54: ## 2. User Personas\n55: \n56: ### P1 — Solo Developer (\"Sam\")\n57: Builds side projects and contract work alone across 3-10 active repos. Switches projects\n58: multiple times a day. Pain: re-explains tooling, conventions, and \"why we built it this\n59: way\" every time they cd into a different directory. Wins by: project-aware context\n60: injection at session start, low-friction `/openltm:memory learn` after a decision.\n61: \n62: ### P2 — Power User / Tooling Hacker (\"Pat\")\n63: Curates their own Claude Code config (hooks, skills, plugins). Wants memory to\n64: **compose** with other plugins, not fight them. Cares about: schema stability, MCP\n65: contract, hook surface, the ability to query the DB directly. Wins by: documented\n66: schema, exportable JSON, FTS5 + semantic search they can trust.\n67: \n68: ### P3 — Team Lead / Tech Lead (\"Tara\")\n69: Drives a small product team (3-8 devs) where AI-assisted coding is the norm. Wants\n70: team-wide consistency on conventions and security gotchas. Today she gets only\n71: per-developer benefit; she wants **shared memory** for \"we agreed to X\" architectural\n72: decisions. Wins by (future): export/import flows, signed memory bundles, project-scoped\n73: shareable decision sets.\n74: \n75: ### P4 — Enterprise / Regulated Dev (\"Ezra\")\n76: Works in an environment with secret-scanning, audit logs, and SOC2 controls. Will not\n77: adopt anything that might silently store secrets, PII, or proprietary code in a sidecar\n78: DB. Wins by: provable redaction, local-only storage, audit trail of writes, ability to\n79: purge per-project or per-time-window.\n80: \n81: ### P5 — Onboarder / New Joiner (\"Noor\")\n82: Just inherited a 5-year-old codebase. Wants to absorb tribal knowledge without reading\n83: every PR. Wins by (future): `git learn` retroactive backfill — turn commit history into\n84: seeded memories with importance and category.\n85: \n86: ---\n87: \n88: ## 3. Jobs to be Done\n89: \n90: The cross-session JTBDs the LTM plugin solves:\n91: \n92: | ID | When... | I want to... | So I can... |\n93: |----|---------|--------------|-------------|\n94: | J1 | I open a new Claude Code session in a project | Have my goal, recent decisions, and active gotchas already in context | Resume work without a 10-minute primer |\n95: | J2 | I make an architectural choice | Capture it once, in 1 keystroke | Stop re-debating it next session |\n96: | J3 | I am about to start a non-trivial task | Be told if we already solved this | Avoid re-doing or contradicting prior work |\n97: | J4 | I get burned by a non-obvious gotcha | Save it as a permanent warning | Never get burned by it again, in any project |\n98: | J5 | I switch from project A to project B | Have B's context auto-restored, A's context not bleed in | Work on the right thing with the right rules |\n99: | J6 | A memory becomes wrong (refactor, pivot) | Forget or supersede it cleanly | Avoid acting on stale advice |\n100: | J7 | I want to know what Claude \"knows\" about this project | See goals, decisions, progress, gotchas at a glance | Trust the system; spot drift |\n101: | J8 | I onboard a new repo | Backfill memory from git history | Get instant institutional knowledge |\n102: | J9 | I worry secrets crept in | Scan the DB and redact in place | Pass an audit; sleep at night |\n103: | J10 | The plugin breaks (hook silent-fail, MCP missing) | Run one diagnostic and get a fix list | Not lose a day debugging meta-tooling |\n104: \n105: ---\n106: \n107: ## 4. Full Feature Inventory (v1.4.20)\n108: \n109: ### 4.1 MCP Tools (server: `src/mcp-server.ts`)\n110: \n111: | Tool | Purpose |\n112: |------|---------|\n113: | `recall` | Search memories by natural-language query. FTS5 + semantic fallback. Filters: project, category, importance. Primary read path. |\n114: | `learn` | Store a new memory. Required: text, category. Optional: importance, project, tags. Auto-redacts secrets on write. |\n115: | `forget` | Soft-delete a memory by id. Used for stale or wrong memories. |\n116: | `relate` | Create a typed edge between two memories (e.g., decision → gotcha). Powers the graph view. |\n117: | `context` | Restore project state at session start: goal + decisions + recent progress + gotchas. |\n118: | `context_items` | List specific context types (goal / decision / progress / gotcha) for a project. |\n119: | `graph` | Traverse memory edges. Used by the visualization server and by Claude when tracing decision chains. |\n120: \n121: ### 4.2 Slash Commands (current grouped surface, v1.4.17+)\n122: \n123: **Active grouped commands:**\n124: | Command | Purpose |\n\n(Showing lines 35-124 of 496. Use offset=125 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"### 1.2 Goals (12-month horizon)\n\n| # | Goal | How we know |\n|---|------|-------------|\n| G1 | Eliminate cross-session amnesia for active projects | 95%+ of sessions on an active project start with relevant context auto-injected |\n| G2 | Make recall faster than re-derivation | Median `recall` round-trip < 200 ms; user reports \"saved me from re-debating X\" |\n| G3 | Keep the developer in flow | Zero mandatory prompts; all LTM ops are background or 1-keystroke |\n| G4 | Survive plugin updates and machine moves | DB at known path, JSON export, schema migrations versioned and idempotent |\n| G5 | Be safe by default | No secret ever lands in the DB; redaction on write; scan command for retroactive cleanup |\n| G6 | Be debuggable in 60 seconds | `/openltm:doctor` and `/openltm:health` give a complete plain-English status |\n\n### 1.3 Non-vision (explicit)\n- This is **not** a team-shared knowledge base (yet). Memory is per-developer-per-machine.\n- This is **not** a replacement for git, code comments, or design docs. It captures the\n  **reasoning behind** the code, not the code itself.\n- This is **not** a model — it is a retrieval and curation layer over a local SQLite store.\n\n---\n\n## 2. User Personas","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/OpenLtm-main/docs/internal/PRD.md","text":"### 1.2 Goals (12-month horizon)\n\n| # | Goal | How we know |\n|---|------|-------------|\n| G1 | Eliminate cross-session amnesia for active projects | 95%+ of sessions on an active project start with relevant context auto-injected |\n| G2 | Make recall faster than re-derivation | Median `recall` round-trip < 200 ms; user reports \"saved me from re-debating X\" |\n| G3 | Keep the developer in flow | Zero mandatory prompts; all LTM ops are background or 1-keystroke |\n| G4 | Survive plugin updates and machine moves | DB at known path, JSON export, schema migrations versioned and idempotent |\n| G5 | Be safe by default | No secret ever lands in the DB; redaction on write; scan command for retroactive cleanup |\n| G6 | Be debuggable in 60 seconds | `/openltm:doctor` and `/openltm:health` give a complete plain-English status |\n\n### 1.3 Non-vision (explicit)\n- This is **not** a team-shared knowledge base (yet). Memory is per-developer-per-machine.\n- This is **not** a replacement for git, code comments, or design docs. It captures the\n  **reasoning behind** the code, not the code itself.\n- This is **not** a model — it is a retrieval and curation layer over a local SQLite store.\n\n---\n\n## 2. User Personas\n\n### P1 — Solo Developer (\"Sam\")\nBuilds side projects and contract work alone across 3-10 active repos. Switches projects\nmultiple times a day. Pain: re-explains tooling, conventions, and \"why we built it this\nway\" every time they cd into a different directory. Wins by: project-aware context\ninjection at session start, low-friction `/openltm:memory learn` after a decision.\n\n### P2 — Power User / Tooling Hacker (\"Pat\")\nCurates their own Claude Code config (hooks, skills, plugins). Wants memory to\n**compose** with other plugins, not fight them. Cares about: schema stability, MCP\ncontract, hook surface, the ability to query the DB directly. Wins by: documented\nschema, exportable JSON, FTS5 + semantic search they can trust.\n\n### P3 — Team Lead / Tech Lead (\"Tara\")\nDrives a small product team (3-8 devs) where AI-assisted coding is the norm. Wants\nteam-wide consistency on conventions and security gotchas. Today she gets only\nper-developer benefit; she wants **shared memory** for \"we agreed to X\" architectural\ndecisions. Wins by (future): export/import flows, signed memory bundles, project-scoped\nshareable decision sets.\n\n### P4 — Enterprise / Regulated Dev (\"Ezra\")\nWorks in an environment with secret-scanning, audit logs, and SOC2 controls. Will not\nadopt anything that might silently store secrets, PII, or proprietary code in a sidecar\nDB. Wins by: provable redaction, local-only storage, audit trail of writes, ability to\npurge per-project or per-time-window.\n\n### P5 — Onboarder / New Joiner (\"Noor\")\nJust inherited a 5-year-old codebase. Wants to absorb tribal knowledge without reading\nevery PR. Wins by (future): `git learn` retroactive backfill — turn commit history into\nseeded memories with importance and category.\n\n---\n\n## 3. Jobs to be Done\n\nThe cross-session JTBDs the LTM plugin solves:\n\n| ID | When... | I want to... | So I can... |\n|----|---------|--------------|-------------|\n| J1 | I open a new Claude Code session in a project | Have my goal, recent decisions, and active gotchas already in context | Resume work without a 10-minute primer |\n| J2 | I make an architectural choice | Capture it once, in 1 keystroke | Stop re-debating it next session |\n| J3 | I am about to start a non-trivial task | Be told if we already solved this | Avoid re-doing or contradicting prior work |\n| J4 | I get burned by a non-obvious gotcha | Save it as a permanent warning | Never get burned by it again, in any project |\n| J5 | I switch from project A to project B | Have B's context auto-restored, A's context not bleed in | Work on the right thing with the right rules |\n| J6 | A memory becomes wrong (refactor, pivot) | Forget or supersede it cleanly | Avoid acting on stale advice |\n| J7 | I want to know what Claude \"knows\" about this project | See goals, decisions, progress, gotchas at a glance | Trust the system; spot drift |\n| J8 | I onboard a new repo | Backfill memory from git history | Get instant institutional knowledge |\n| J9 | I worry secrets crept in | Scan the DB and redact in place | Pass an audit; sleep at night |\n| J10 | The plugin breaks (hook silent-fail, MCP missing) | Run one diagnostic and get a fix list | Not lose a day debugging meta-tooling |\n\n---\n\n## 4. Full Feature Inventory (v1.4.20)\n\n### 4.1 MCP Tools (server: `src/mcp-server.ts`)\n\n| Tool | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `recall` | Search memories by natural-language query. FTS5 + semantic fallback. Filters: project, category, importance. Primary read path. |\n| `learn` | Store a new memory. Required: text, category. Optional: importance, project, tags. Auto-redacts secrets on write. |\n| `forget` | Soft-delete a memory by id. Used for stale or wrong memories. |\n| `relate` | Create a typed edge between two memories (e.g., decision → gotcha). Powers the graph view. |\n| `context` | Restore project state at session start: goal + decisions + recent progress + gotchas. |\n| `context_items` | List specific context types (goal / decision / progress / gotcha) for a project. |\n| `graph` | Traverse memory edges. Used by the visualization server and by Claude when tracing decision chains. |\n\n### 4.2 Slash Commands (current grouped surface, v1.4.17+)\n\n**Active grouped commands:**\n| Command | Purpose |","lineStart":35,"lineEnd":124,"totalLines":496,"truncated":true}},"title":"specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/OpenLtm-main/docs/internal/PRD.md","time":{"start":1780925723802,"end":1780925723812}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_01762d7c6b951c3c016a26c51bbe688191aadaf81fc7a4af8e"}},"id":"prt_ea771f492001EYik3064TQTohG","sessionID":"ses_158903c24ffeYh4HmE3B8vB3CW","messageID":"msg_ea771c25c0013tqUGmFPfMmFrr"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780925723852,"sessionID":"ses_158903c24ffeYh4HmE3B8vB3CW","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_JpmaA0gkk5cZqZcWsiepJRXk","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/OpenLtm-main/docs/internal/PRD.md","offset":386,"limit":45},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/OpenLtm-main/docs/internal/PRD.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n386: ### G-L — Memory budget + compression\n387: When DB grows past a threshold, summarize clusters of related decisions into a\n388: single rolled-up memory, archive originals. **Why magnificent:** memory grows\n389: sub-linearly with project age.\n390: \n391: ### G-M — Cross-plugin memory contract\n392: Publish a stable read-API so other plugins (e.g., dev-team task-tracker, code-review)\n393: can write into LTM with proper category and source tag. **Why magnificent:** LTM\n394: becomes the substrate for the whole Claude Code ecosystem, not a silo.\n395: \n396: ### G-N — Magnificent UI: graph-app v2\n397: The current graph-app exists but is utilitarian. v2: timeline scrubber, search\n398: overlay, force-directed clustering by category, click-through to invoking session.\n399: **Owned by:** ui-ux-designer.\n400: \n401: ### G-O — Onboarding wizard\n402: First-run flow: detect projects in a chosen dir, prompt to register, run GitLearn\n403: backfill, surface first 5 candidate memories for confirmation. **Why magnificent:**\n404: new users get value in the first 5 minutes, not the first month.\n405: \n406: ---\n407: \n408: ## 7. Non-Goals\n409: \n410: The plugin will not, in this PRD horizon:\n411: \n412: - **N1.** Send memories to any third-party cloud by default.\n413: - **N2.** Replace ADRs, design docs, code comments, or commit messages.\n414: - **N3.** Operate as a multi-tenant team-shared store. (G-A explores a bundle export\n415:   flow, but the live store is per-developer-per-machine.)\n416: - **N4.** Run a model locally for embeddings — embeddings either come from Claude's\n417:   own tools or a deterministic fallback. No bundled ML runtime.\n418: - **N5.** Modify source code automatically based on memory contents.\n419: - **N6.** Capture or store full conversation transcripts. The LTM is for **distilled**\n420:   insights, not raw history.\n421: - **N7.** Provide guarantees around hostile inputs (malicious memory poisoning) beyond\n422:   basic redaction. Threat model is single-developer, locally trusted environment.\n423: - **N8.** Replace the `task-tracker` MCP, the `context-mode` MCP, or any other plugin's\n424:   responsibility. LTM is one slice of the stack.\n425: \n426: ---\n427: \n428: ## 8. Success Metrics\n429: \n430: Leading indicators (engagement / activation) come first; lagging indicators (durable\n\n(Showing lines 386-430 of 496. Use offset=431 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"### G-L — Memory budget + compression\nWhen DB grows past a threshold, summarize clusters of related decisions into a\nsingle rolled-up memory, archive originals. **Why magnificent:** memory grows\nsub-linearly with project age.\n\n### G-M — Cross-plugin memory contract\nPublish a stable read-API so other plugins (e.g., dev-team task-tracker, code-review)\ncan write into LTM with proper category and source tag. **Why magnificent:** LTM\nbecomes the substrate for the whole Claude Code ecosystem, not a silo.\n\n### G-N — Magnificent UI: graph-app v2\nThe current graph-app exists but is utilitarian. v2: timeline scrubber, search\noverlay, force-directed clustering by category, click-through to invoking session.\n**Owned by:** ui-ux-designer.\n\n### G-O — Onboarding wizard\nFirst-run flow: detect projects in a chosen dir, prompt to register, run GitLearn\nbackfill, surface first 5 candidate memories for confirmation. **Why magnificent:**\nnew users get value in the first 5 minutes, not the first month.\n","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/OpenLtm-main/docs/internal/PRD.md","text":"### G-L — Memory budget + compression\nWhen DB grows past a threshold, summarize clusters of related decisions into a\nsingle rolled-up memory, archive originals. **Why magnificent:** memory grows\nsub-linearly with project age.\n\n### G-M — Cross-plugin memory contract\nPublish a stable read-API so other plugins (e.g., dev-team task-tracker, code-review)\ncan write into LTM with proper category and source tag. **Why magnificent:** LTM\nbecomes the substrate for the whole Claude Code ecosystem, not a silo.\n\n### G-N — Magnificent UI: graph-app v2\nThe current graph-app exists but is utilitarian. v2: timeline scrubber, search\noverlay, force-directed clustering by category, click-through to invoking session.\n**Owned by:** ui-ux-designer.\n\n### G-O — Onboarding wizard\nFirst-run flow: detect projects in a chosen dir, prompt to register, run GitLearn\nbackfill, surface first 5 candidate memories for confirmation. **Why magnificent:**\nnew users get value in the first 5 minutes, not the first month.\n\n---\n\n## 7. Non-Goals\n\nThe plugin will not, in this PRD horizon:\n\n- **N1.** Send memories to any third-party cloud by default.\n- **N2.** Replace ADRs, design docs, code comments, or commit messages.\n- **N3.** Operate as a multi-tenant team-shared store. (G-A explores a bundle export\n  flow, but the live store is per-developer-per-machine.)\n- **N4.** Run a model locally for embeddings — embeddings either come from Claude's\n  own tools or a deterministic fallback. No bundled ML runtime.\n- **N5.** Modify source code automatically based on memory contents.\n- **N6.** Capture or store full conversation transcripts. The LTM is for **distilled**\n  insights, not raw history.\n- **N7.** Provide guarantees around hostile inputs (malicious memory poisoning) beyond\n  basic redaction. Threat model is single-developer, locally trusted environment.\n- **N8.** Replace the `task-tracker` MCP, the `context-mode` MCP, or any other plugin's\n  responsibility. LTM is one slice of the stack.\n\n---\n\n## 8. Success Metrics\n\nLeading indicators (engagement / activation) come first; lagging indicators (durable","lineStart":386,"lineEnd":430,"totalLines":496,"truncated":true}},"title":"specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/OpenLtm-main/docs/internal/PRD.md","time":{"start":1780925723841,"end":1780925723851}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_01762d7c6b951c3c016a26c51bbe7c8191832d9eb23bed5728"}},"id":"prt_ea771f4ba001uhvn0oNmhUcUjp","sessionID":"ses_158903c24ffeYh4HmE3B8vB3CW","messageID":"msg_ea771c25c0013tqUGmFPfMmFrr"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780925723876,"sessionID":"ses_158903c24ffeYh4HmE3B8vB3CW","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_ZU9lKwytuHE2GqxuvTZIJI4k","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/OpenLtm-main/docs/internal/ROADMAP.md","offset":1,"limit":80},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/OpenLtm-main/docs/internal/ROADMAP.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # ROADMAP — OpenLTM Plugin\n2: \n3: > **Master integration spec.** Synthesises `PRD.md`, `ARCHITECTURE.md`, `UX-SPEC.md` into a single phased plan. `DB-SPEC.md` augments §6 (Schema) and per-phase DB work once written.\n4: >\n5: > Source documents — keep authoritative:\n6: > - `docs/internal/PRD.md` — what & why (vision, personas, JTBDs, US-1..17, gaps G-A..G-O)\n7: > - `docs/03-architecture.md` — system shape (C4, ADR-001..006, weaknesses W1..W12, capabilities C1..C10)\n8: > - `docs/internal/UX-SPEC.md` — user-facing surface (interaction model, hooks, surfaces S1..S5)\n9: > - `docs/internal/DB-SPEC.md` — schema (pending; section 6 + per-phase DB rows updated when ready)\n10: \n11: ---\n12: \n13: ## 1. Executive Summary\n14: \n15: **Where we are (v1.4.20):** A working LTM plugin with SQLite + FTS5 + 4 hooks + 7 MCP tools + grouped commands. Functional. Honest weaknesses: silent hook failures, hand-rolled migrations, O(N) recall, no provenance, no audit, no observability. UX is invisible-by-default but onboarding is \"abandoned by 50%\".\n16: \n17: **Where we want to be:** A magnificent LTM that is invisible when it should be, surgical when invoked, trustable for teams and enterprise, and pluggable for embeddings, sync, bundles, and cross-plugin contracts.\n18: \n19: **The plan:** 8 phases (v1.5.x → v2.2.x). Phases 0–4 are non-breaking foundation. Phase 5 (v2.0.0) is the semver-major cross-plugin contract. Phases 6–7 layer on team/enterprise/power-user features.\n20: \n21: ---\n22: \n23: ## 2. Unified Work Inventory\n24: \n25: The four source docs catalogue overlapping concerns from different angles. This table maps every issue/feature to its owners across docs.\n26: \n27: | Theme | PRD gap | Arch weakness | Arch capability | UX surface | DB impact |\n28: |---|---|---|---|---|---|\n29: | Migration framework | — | W3 | (Phase 0) | §6.3 errors | TBD §5 |\n30: | Recall scoring at scale | — | W4 | C8 explainer | §8.3 S2 | TBD §4 (decay_score) |\n31: | Embedding-based recall | G-E | (impl in C1) | C1 | §8.3 S2 | TBD §7 (memory_embeddings) |\n32: | Provenance | G-J | W9 | C5 | §8.4 S3 review | TBD §7 (memory_audit) |\n33: | Audit trail | — | W11 | C5 | §6 errors | TBD §7 (memory_audit) |\n34: | Observability | — | W5 | (Phase 1) | §3 hook map, §6.5 silent-fail | — |\n35: | MCP response bloat | — | W7 | (Phase 1 DAO) | §2.1 recall latency | TBD §7 (split embeddings) |\n36: | Hook failure visibility | — | W1 | (Phase 1) | §3 hook UX, §6.1 | — |\n37: | Concurrent writes | — | W2, W12 | (Phase 0) | §6.4 lifecycle | TBD §6 (locking) |\n38: | Cache vs source dual-write | — | W6 | (Phase 5) | §6.4 lifecycle | — |\n39: | Hook ↔ schema coupling | — | W8 | (Phase 1 DAO) | — | — |\n40: | EvaluateSession policy | — | W10 | (Phase 0) | §3.3 (propose-not-write) | — |\n41: | Auto-categorisation | G-C | — | (Phase 3) | §8.2 ambient | — |\n42: | Negative memories | G-D | — | C4 conflict | §8.3 S2 | TBD §7 (conflict tables) |\n43: | Conflict detection | G-F | — | C4 | §8.3 S2 conflict modal | TBD §7 |\n44: | Memory diffing | G-B | — | C10 | §8.4 S3 review | — |\n45: | Replay mode | G-G | — | C9 | §8.4 S3 | TBD §9 (time-travel) |\n46: | Pre-commit \"did you learn this?\" | G-H | — | (Phase 6) | §8 ambient | — |\n47: | Cloud sync (E2E) | G-I | — | C2 | §8.6 S4 team | TBD §7 (sync tables) |\n48: | Memory budget / compression | G-L | — | C6 | §8.8 defaults | TBD §8 scale |\n49: | Cross-plugin contract | G-M | — | C7 | §8.7 surfaces | TBD §9 (versioning) |\n50: | Team bundles | G-A | — | C3 | §8.6 S4 | TBD §7 (team_bundles) |\n51: | Graph-app v2 | G-N | — | (Phase 6) | §8.7 inventory | — |\n52: | Onboarding wizard | G-O | — | (Phase 0) | §5, §8.5 | — |\n53: | Cognitive load reduction | — | — | — | §9 (40→17 concepts) | — |\n54: \n55: ---\n56: \n57: ## 3. The 8-Phase Roadmap\n58: \n59: Each phase aligns with `ARCHITECTURE.md §9`. Versions are guidance; ship cadence is per-phase, not per-feature.\n60: \n61: ### Phase 0 — Foundation Hardening (v1.5.x, non-breaking)\n62: \n63: **Goal:** Stop the bleeding. Fix the things that silently lose data or fail without telling anyone.\n64: \n65: | Source | Item |\n66: |---|---|\n67: | Arch | W1 surface hook errors to user (panel + log path) |\n68: | Arch | W2 advisory lock around `registry.json` writes |\n69: | Arch | W3 `migration_history` table + versioned migration files (replaces hand-rolled ALTERs) |\n70: | Arch | W10 Lock down `EvaluateSession` policy: **propose, do not auto-write** (resolves UX-SPEC §3.3) |\n71: | Arch | W12 Single-process write coordinator (mutex / write queue) |\n72: | UX | §6.5 Silent-failure audit — every catch block emits a visible result |\n73: | UX | §3.1 SessionStart panel: explicit \"context restored / not restored\" line |\n74: | PRD | G-O onboarding wizard v1 (terminal walkthrough, 5 steps) |\n75: \n76: **Exit criteria:** zero silent hook failures in 1 week of dogfooding · migration history table is the source of truth · EvaluateSession never writes without a confirmation step.\n77: \n78: ---\n79: \n80: ### Phase 1 — DAO + Observability (v1.6.x, non-breaking)\n\n(Showing lines 1-80 of 266. Use offset=81 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# ROADMAP — OpenLTM Plugin\n\n> **Master integration spec.** Synthesises `PRD.md`, `ARCHITECTURE.md`, `UX-SPEC.md` into a single phased plan. `DB-SPEC.md` augments §6 (Schema) and per-phase DB work once written.\n>\n> Source documents — keep authoritative:\n> - `docs/internal/PRD.md` — what & why (vision, personas, JTBDs, US-1..17, gaps G-A..G-O)\n> - `docs/03-architecture.md` — system shape (C4, ADR-001..006, weaknesses W1..W12, capabilities C1..C10)\n> - `docs/internal/UX-SPEC.md` — user-facing surface (interaction model, hooks, surfaces S1..S5)\n> - `docs/internal/DB-SPEC.md` — schema (pending; section 6 + per-phase DB rows updated when ready)\n\n---\n\n## 1. Executive Summary\n\n**Where we are (v1.4.20):** A working LTM plugin with SQLite + FTS5 + 4 hooks + 7 MCP tools + grouped commands. Functional. Honest weaknesses: silent hook failures, hand-rolled migrations, O(N) recall, no provenance, no audit, no observability. UX is invisible-by-default but onboarding is \"abandoned by 50%\".\n\n**Where we want to be:** A magnificent LTM that is invisible when it should be, surgical when invoked, trustable for teams and enterprise, and pluggable for embeddings, sync, bundles, and cross-plugin contracts.\n\n**The plan:** 8 phases (v1.5.x → v2.2.x). Phases 0–4 are non-breaking foundation. Phase 5 (v2.0.0) is the semver-major cross-plugin contract. Phases 6–7 layer on team/enterprise/power-user features.\n","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/OpenLtm-main/docs/internal/ROADMAP.md","text":"# ROADMAP — OpenLTM Plugin\n\n> **Master integration spec.** Synthesises `PRD.md`, `ARCHITECTURE.md`, `UX-SPEC.md` into a single phased plan. `DB-SPEC.md` augments §6 (Schema) and per-phase DB work once written.\n>\n> Source documents — keep authoritative:\n> - `docs/internal/PRD.md` — what & why (vision, personas, JTBDs, US-1..17, gaps G-A..G-O)\n> - `docs/03-architecture.md` — system shape (C4, ADR-001..006, weaknesses W1..W12, capabilities C1..C10)\n> - `docs/internal/UX-SPEC.md` — user-facing surface (interaction model, hooks, surfaces S1..S5)\n> - `docs/internal/DB-SPEC.md` — schema (pending; section 6 + per-phase DB rows updated when ready)\n\n---\n\n## 1. Executive Summary\n\n**Where we are (v1.4.20):** A working LTM plugin with SQLite + FTS5 + 4 hooks + 7 MCP tools + grouped commands. Functional. Honest weaknesses: silent hook failures, hand-rolled migrations, O(N) recall, no provenance, no audit, no observability. UX is invisible-by-default but onboarding is \"abandoned by 50%\".\n\n**Where we want to be:** A magnificent LTM that is invisible when it should be, surgical when invoked, trustable for teams and enterprise, and pluggable for embeddings, sync, bundles, and cross-plugin contracts.\n\n**The plan:** 8 phases (v1.5.x → v2.2.x). Phases 0–4 are non-breaking foundation. Phase 5 (v2.0.0) is the semver-major cross-plugin contract. Phases 6–7 layer on team/enterprise/power-user features.\n\n---\n\n## 2. Unified Work Inventory\n\nThe four source docs catalogue overlapping concerns from different angles. This table maps every issue/feature to its owners across docs.\n\n| Theme | PRD gap | Arch weakness | Arch capability | UX surface | DB impact |\n|---|---|---|---|---|---|\n| Migration framework | — | W3 | (Phase 0) | §6.3 errors | TBD §5 |\n| Recall scoring at scale | — | W4 | C8 explainer | §8.3 S2 | TBD §4 (decay_score) |\n| Embedding-based recall | G-E | (impl in C1) | C1 | §8.3 S2 | TBD §7 (memory_embeddings) |\n| Provenance | G-J | W9 | C5 | §8.4 S3 review | TBD §7 (memory_audit) |\n| Audit trail | — | W11 | C5 | §6 errors | TBD §7 (memory_audit) |\n| Observability | — | W5 | (Phase 1) | §3 hook map, §6.5 silent-fail | — |\n| MCP response bloat | — | W7 | (Phase 1 DAO) | §2.1 recall latency | TBD §7 (split embeddings) |\n| Hook failure visibility | — | W1 | (Phase 1) | §3 hook UX, §6.1 | — |\n| Concurrent writes | — | W2, W12 | (Phase 0) | §6.4 lifecycle | TBD §6 (locking) |\n| Cache vs source dual-write | — | W6 | (Phase 5) | §6.4 lifecycle | — |\n| Hook ↔ schema coupling | — | W8 | (Phase 1 DAO) | — | — |\n| EvaluateSession policy | — | W10 | (Phase 0) | §3.3 (propose-not-write) | — |\n| Auto-categorisation | G-C | — | (Phase 3) | §8.2 ambient | — |\n| Negative memories | G-D | — | C4 conflict | §8.3 S2 | TBD §7 (conflict tables) |\n| Conflict detection | G-F | — | C4 | §8.3 S2 conflict modal | TBD §7 |\n| Memory diffing | G-B | — | C10 | §8.4 S3 review | — |\n| Replay mode | G-G | — | C9 | §8.4 S3 | TBD §9 (time-travel) |\n| Pre-commit \"did you learn this?\" | G-H | — | (Phase 6) | §8 ambient | — |\n| Cloud sync (E2E) | G-I | — | C2 | §8.6 S4 team | TBD §7 (sync tables) |\n| Memory budget / compression | G-L | — | C6 | §8.8 defaults | TBD §8 scale |\n| Cross-plugin contract | G-M | — | C7 | §8.7 surfaces | TBD §9 (versioning) |\n| Team bundles | G-A | — | C3 | §8.6 S4 | TBD §7 (team_bundles) |\n| Graph-app v2 | G-N | — | (Phase 6) | §8.7 inventory | — |\n| Onboarding wizard | G-O | — | (Phase 0) | §5, §8.5 | — |\n| Cognitive load reduction | — | — | — | §9 (40→17 concepts) | — |\n\n---\n\n## 3. The 8-Phase Roadmap\n\nEach phase aligns with `ARCHITECTURE.md §9`. Versions are guidance; ship cadence is per-phase, not per-feature.\n\n### Phase 0 — Foundation Hardening (v1.5.x, non-breaking)\n\n**Goal:** Stop the bleeding. Fix the things that silently lose data or fail without telling anyone.\n\n| Source | Item |\n|---|---|\n| Arch | W1 surface hook errors to user (panel + log path) |\n| Arch | W2 advisory lock around `registry.json` writes |\n| Arch | W3 `migration_history` table + versioned migration files (replaces hand-rolled ALTERs) |\n| Arch | W10 Lock down `EvaluateSession` policy: **propose, do not auto-write** (resolves UX-SPEC §3.3) |\n| Arch | W12 Single-process write coordinator (mutex / write queue) |\n| UX | §6.5 Silent-failure audit — every catch block emits a visible result |\n| UX | §3.1 SessionStart panel: explicit \"context restored / not restored\" line |\n| PRD | G-O onboarding wizard v1 (terminal walkthrough, 5 steps) |\n\n**Exit criteria:** zero silent hook failures in 1 week of dogfooding · migration history table is the source of truth · EvaluateSession never writes without a confirmation step.\n\n---\n\n### Phase 1 — DAO + Observability (v1.6.x, non-breaking)","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":80,"totalLines":266,"truncated":true}},"title":"specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/OpenLtm-main/docs/internal/ROADMAP.md","time":{"start":1780925723869,"end":1780925723873}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_01762d7c6b951c3c016a26c51bbe848191a2ca29e749fae465"}},"id":"prt_ea771f4c2001JURzYy5kCb9DiG","sessionID":"ses_158903c24ffeYh4HmE3B8vB3CW","messageID":"msg_ea771c25c0013tqUGmFPfMmFrr"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780925723919,"sessionID":"ses_158903c24ffeYh4HmE3B8vB3CW","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_1UDXNQocHFu1Ibr5pyuK1hge","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/OpenLtm-main/docs/internal/ROADMAP.md","offset":140,"limit":75},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/OpenLtm-main/docs/internal/ROADMAP.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n140: \n141: **Exit criteria:** recall scoring is O(top-k log N) not O(N) · DB size growth flattens at scale · janitor logs visible in `/openltm:health`.\n142: \n143: ---\n144: \n145: ### Phase 5 — Cross-Plugin Contract (v2.0.0, semver-major)\n146: \n147: **Goal:** LTM becomes a contract. Other plugins read/write memories through a versioned interface.\n148: \n149: | Source | Item |\n150: |---|---|\n151: | Arch | C7 Cross-plugin memory contract (versioned MCP API + capability discovery) |\n152: | PRD | G-M cross-plugin memory contract |\n153: | Arch | W6 Resolve cache vs source-repo dual-write (single execution model) |\n154: | UX | §9 cognitive load reduction — drop the `:memory:` subnamespace, consolidate to ~17 concepts |\n155: | UX | §7.3 sunset timeline — deprecated aliases removed at 2.0.0 |\n156: \n157: **Exit criteria:** another plugin can recall+learn through the contract without coupling · breaking changes documented in MIGRATION.md · all UX-SPEC §7 deprecations sunset.\n158: \n159: ---\n160: \n161: ### Phase 6 — Sync + Bundles (v2.1.x, non-breaking on contract)\n162: \n163: **Goal:** Multi-device. Team-shareable.\n164: \n165: | Source | Item |\n166: |---|---|\n167: | Arch | C2 Multi-device E2E encrypted sync |\n168: | Arch | C3 Team memory bundles (signed export/import) |\n169: | Arch | C4 Conflict detection on learn |\n170: | PRD | G-A team-shared memory bundles |\n171: | PRD | G-F conflict detection on learn |\n172: | PRD | G-I privacy-safe cloud sync (opt-in) |\n173: | PRD | G-D negative memories (\"we tried X, it failed because Y\") |\n174: | PRD | G-H pre-commit \"did you learn this?\" hook |\n175: | UX | §8.6 S4 team handoff |\n176: | PRD | G-N graph-app v2 |\n177: | DB | sync tables, team_bundles, conflict tables (pending DB-SPEC §7) |\n178: \n179: **Exit criteria:** two devices stay in sync · a team can import a signed bundle and reject it on signature mismatch · conflict modal renders on duplicate learn.\n180: \n181: ---\n182: \n183: ### Phase 7 — Time-Travel + Diffing (v2.2.x, non-breaking)\n184: \n185: **Goal:** Memory becomes history. You can replay it, diff it, audit it.\n186: \n187: | Source | Item |\n188: |---|---|\n189: | Arch | C9 Time-travel replay — re-create a session's memory state at a point in time |\n190: | Arch | C10 Memory diffing across versions |\n191: | PRD | G-G `memory replay` mode |\n192: | PRD | G-B memory diffing across versions |\n193: | UX | §8.4 S3 Memory Review UI surfaces diff/replay |\n194: | DB | versioning tables (pending DB-SPEC §9) |\n195: \n196: **Exit criteria:** `/openltm:memory replay --at 2026-04-01` reconstructs the memory set as it was · diff between two memory snapshots renders.\n197: \n198: ---\n199: \n200: ## 4. Cross-Cutting Workstreams (run alongside all phases)\n201: \n202: ### 4.1 UX Cognitive Load Reduction (UX-SPEC §9)\n203: - Drop `:memory:` subnamespace by Phase 5\n204: - Consolidate 40 concepts → 17 (5 commands, 4 categories, 5 link types, 3 weight tiers)\n205: - Naming cleanups across deprecated aliases\n206: \n207: ### 4.2 Discoverability (UX-SPEC §5)\n208: - Phase 0: terminal onboarding wizard\n209: - Phase 3: ambient suggestion panel (S1)\n210: - Phase 6: graph-app v2 (G-N)\n211: \n212: ### 4.3 Trust & Transparency (UX-SPEC §6 + Arch W11/C5)\n213: - Phase 0: silent-failure audit\n214: - Phase 2: provenance + audit\n\n(Showing lines 140-214 of 266. Use offset=215 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"\n**Exit criteria:** recall scoring is O(top-k log N) not O(N) · DB size growth flattens at scale · janitor logs visible in `/openltm:health`.\n\n---\n\n### Phase 5 — Cross-Plugin Contract (v2.0.0, semver-major)\n\n**Goal:** LTM becomes a contract. Other plugins read/write memories through a versioned interface.\n\n| Source | Item |\n|---|---|\n| Arch | C7 Cross-plugin memory contract (versioned MCP API + capability discovery) |\n| PRD | G-M cross-plugin memory contract |\n| Arch | W6 Resolve cache vs source-repo dual-write (single execution model) |\n| UX | §9 cognitive load reduction — drop the `:memory:` subnamespace, consolidate to ~17 concepts |\n| UX | §7.3 sunset timeline — deprecated aliases removed at 2.0.0 |\n\n**Exit criteria:** another plugin can recall+learn through the contract without coupling · breaking changes documented in MIGRATION.md · all UX-SPEC §7 deprecations sunset.\n\n---","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/OpenLtm-main/docs/internal/ROADMAP.md","text":"\n**Exit criteria:** recall scoring is O(top-k log N) not O(N) · DB size growth flattens at scale · janitor logs visible in `/openltm:health`.\n\n---\n\n### Phase 5 — Cross-Plugin Contract (v2.0.0, semver-major)\n\n**Goal:** LTM becomes a contract. Other plugins read/write memories through a versioned interface.\n\n| Source | Item |\n|---|---|\n| Arch | C7 Cross-plugin memory contract (versioned MCP API + capability discovery) |\n| PRD | G-M cross-plugin memory contract |\n| Arch | W6 Resolve cache vs source-repo dual-write (single execution model) |\n| UX | §9 cognitive load reduction — drop the `:memory:` subnamespace, consolidate to ~17 concepts |\n| UX | §7.3 sunset timeline — deprecated aliases removed at 2.0.0 |\n\n**Exit criteria:** another plugin can recall+learn through the contract without coupling · breaking changes documented in MIGRATION.md · all UX-SPEC §7 deprecations sunset.\n\n---\n\n### Phase 6 — Sync + Bundles (v2.1.x, non-breaking on contract)\n\n**Goal:** Multi-device. Team-shareable.\n\n| Source | Item |\n|---|---|\n| Arch | C2 Multi-device E2E encrypted sync |\n| Arch | C3 Team memory bundles (signed export/import) |\n| Arch | C4 Conflict detection on learn |\n| PRD | G-A team-shared memory bundles |\n| PRD | G-F conflict detection on learn |\n| PRD | G-I privacy-safe cloud sync (opt-in) |\n| PRD | G-D negative memories (\"we tried X, it failed because Y\") |\n| PRD | G-H pre-commit \"did you learn this?\" hook |\n| UX | §8.6 S4 team handoff |\n| PRD | G-N graph-app v2 |\n| DB | sync tables, team_bundles, conflict tables (pending DB-SPEC §7) |\n\n**Exit criteria:** two devices stay in sync · a team can import a signed bundle and reject it on signature mismatch · conflict modal renders on duplicate learn.\n\n---\n\n### Phase 7 — Time-Travel + Diffing (v2.2.x, non-breaking)\n\n**Goal:** Memory becomes history. You can replay it, diff it, audit it.\n\n| Source | Item |\n|---|---|\n| Arch | C9 Time-travel replay — re-create a session's memory state at a point in time |\n| Arch | C10 Memory diffing across versions |\n| PRD | G-G `memory replay` mode |\n| PRD | G-B memory diffing across versions |\n| UX | §8.4 S3 Memory Review UI surfaces diff/replay |\n| DB | versioning tables (pending DB-SPEC §9) |\n\n**Exit criteria:** `/openltm:memory replay --at 2026-04-01` reconstructs the memory set as it was · diff between two memory snapshots renders.\n\n---\n\n## 4. Cross-Cutting Workstreams (run alongside all phases)\n\n### 4.1 UX Cognitive Load Reduction (UX-SPEC §9)\n- Drop `:memory:` subnamespace by Phase 5\n- Consolidate 40 concepts → 17 (5 commands, 4 categories, 5 link types, 3 weight tiers)\n- Naming cleanups across deprecated aliases\n\n### 4.2 Discoverability (UX-SPEC §5)\n- Phase 0: terminal onboarding wizard\n- Phase 3: ambient suggestion panel (S1)\n- Phase 6: graph-app v2 (G-N)\n\n### 4.3 Trust & Transparency (UX-SPEC §6 + Arch W11/C5)\n- Phase 0: silent-failure audit\n- Phase 2: provenance + audit","lineStart":140,"lineEnd":214,"totalLines":266,"truncated":true}},"title":"specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/OpenLtm-main/docs/internal/ROADMAP.md","time":{"start":1780925723902,"end":1780925723916}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_01762d7c6b951c3c016a26c51bbe8c81918d80eff4ed0f692f"}},"id":"prt_ea771f4e9001a4kvDci8dHBlfr","sessionID":"ses_158903c24ffeYh4HmE3B8vB3CW","messageID":"msg_ea771c25c0013tqUGmFPfMmFrr"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780925723919,"sessionID":"ses_158903c24ffeYh4HmE3B8vB3CW","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_h7suULexyAzMKMUHgyUnPhaP","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/OpenLtm-main/docs/internal/ROADMAP.md","offset":245,"limit":15},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/OpenLtm-main/docs/internal/ROADMAP.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n245: | Phase 0 | §5 migration system | `schema_migrations` table + versioned migration runner |\n246: | Phase 0 | §2 indexes | 4 missing indexes added: `idx_memories_status_importance`, `idx_memories_created_at`, `idx_memories_last_recalled_at`, `idx_ctx_project_type_created` |\n247: | Phase 0 | §6 concurrency | `BEGIN IMMEDIATE`, atomic rename for registry, WAL semantics documented |\n248: | Phase 1 | §1 + §2 | DAO splits expensive columns (embeddings, audit) from hot paths |\n249: | Phase 2 | §7 audit/provenance | `memory_provenance`, `memory_audit` tables (DDL in DB-SPEC §7) |\n250: | Phase 3 | §7 embeddings | `memory_embeddings` table split from `memories`; multi-column FTS rebuild |\n251: | Phase 4 | §4 decay | Materialised `decay_score` column + janitor refresh job |\n252: | Phase 5 | §1 contract | `projects`, `hook_events` tables stabilised at 2.0.0 |\n253: | Phase 6 | §7 sync/bundles | `team_bundles`, `bundle_memories`, `signing_keys`, `memory_conflicts`, `sync_state`, `sync_ops` |\n254: | Phase 7 | §7 versioning | `memory_snapshots`, `snapshot_memories` |\n255: \n256: DB-SPEC §9 sequences 19 migration files across these phases — that file is the migration order of record.\n257: \n258: ---\n259: \n\n(Showing lines 245-259 of 266. Use offset=260 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"| Phase 0 | §5 migration system | `schema